pdc_discovery.title: Ensure that the deprecated Solr Collection pdc-discovery-production-1 is deleted
Possible caching issue when using widgets to filter

comments.body:
The problem is because our two replicas are out of synch:
* lib-solr-prod5 reports 362 documents total
* lib-solr-prod6 reports 231 documents total
I am not sure how they got out of synch...still troubleshooting.

> The problem is because our two replicas are out of synch:
> 
> * lib-solr-prod5 reports 362 documents total
> * lib-solr-prod6 reports 231 documents total
>   I am not sure how they got out of synch...still troubleshooting.

Thanks for investigating.

@jrgriffiniii and I identified an issue with the replication configuration for PDC Describe and fixed it via this PR https://github.com/pulibrary/pul_solr/pull/357. 

After that we created a new Solr collection `pdc-discovery-production-2` (with 1 shard, 2 replicas) and reindexed the data there to confirm that the replication works as expected. Once we confirmed it is working we created a new alias to point to to this new collection. 

Tomorrow we'll delete the old collection (see https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_discovery/issues/414)

See also [our incident notes](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YRBHCrDbU6tGQHE_ddH7Odha_Yy4SjgFenS_s6HtzyI/edit#heading=h.dekaki8n3kzl)

comments.body:

```bash
[thesiscentralsu@libtc201l Vireo]$ :: loading settings :: url = jar:file:/home/thesiscentralsu/play1-1.3.0/framework/lib/ivy-2.3.0.jar!/org/apache/ivy/core/sett
ings/ivysettings.xml
Exception in thread "main" play.exceptions.DatabaseException: Cannot connected t
o the database[default], Connections could not be acquired from the underlying d
atabase!
        at play.db.DBPlugin.onApplicationStart(DBPlugin.java:196)
        at play.plugins.PluginCollection.onApplicationStart(PluginCollection.jav
a:515)
        at play.Play.start(Play.java:537)
        at play.Play.init(Play.java:309)
        at play.server.Server.main(Server.java:160)
Caused by: java.sql.SQLException: Connections could not be acquired from the und
erlying database!
        at com.mchange.v2.sql.SqlUtils.toSQLException(SqlUtils.java:118)
        at play.db.DBPlugin.onApplicationStart(DBPlugin.java:179)
        ... 4 more
Caused by: com.mchange.v2.resourcepool.CannotAcquireResourceException: A Resourc
ePool could not acquire a resource from its primary factory or source.
        at com.mchange.v2.resourcepool.BasicResourcePool.awaitAvailable(BasicRes
ourcePool.java:1463)
```

I truly do not understand why the connection is failing from inside of the application:

```bash
[thesiscentralsu@libtc201l Vireo]$ psql -h theses-central-2020.ct9hnzmkuoct.us-e
ast-1.rds.amazonaws.com -W -U thesis-prod thesis-prod-db
```

The database URL and credentials are being properly passed to the application here:

https://github.com/playframework/play1/blob/629aee531fd3290113bedff97f7d762646304ed9/framework/pym/play/application.py#L29
